WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.835 --> 00:00:03.633
Previously on "Constantine.."

2
00:00:03.837 --> 00:00:05.259
My name is John Constantine.

3
00:00:05.464 --> 00:00:07.137
"Exorcist. demonologist

4
00:00:07.341 --> 00:00:09.844
and master of the dark arts?"

5
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.262
There's a darkness rising. John.

6
00:00:11.470 --> 00:00:12.767
People can sense
what's on the way.

7
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.598
It's happening everywhere.

8
00:00:14.806 --> 00:00:16.228
If you figure out
what we're up against

9
00:00:16.433 --> 00:00:18.606
I will use that knowledge
to save lives.

10
00:00:18.810 --> 00:00:21.609
- What about my life. eh?
- 'You damned a girl to hell.

11
00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:24.692
And along with her. your soul.
At least for a moment. anyway.

12
00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:25.947
Are you suggesting that
it's not too late

13
00:00:26.151 --> 00:00:27.323
for me to save my soul?

14
00:00:27.528 --> 00:00:29.121
That mean
you're going to help us?

15
00:00:29.321 --> 00:00:31.244
I walk my path alone.

16
00:00:31.448 --> 00:00:33.291
Because. let's be honest

17
00:00:33.492 --> 00:00:35.995
who would be crazy enough
to walk it with me?

18
00:00:57.140 --> 00:00:59.188
Bad clay?

19
00:01:01.353 --> 00:01:03.151
Lannis?

20
00:01:03.355 --> 00:01:05.403
Three more on my shift
threatened to quit today.

21
00:01:05.607 --> 00:01:08.611
Candy asses.

22
00:01:08.819 --> 00:01:09.866
They still hearing the sounds?

23
00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:11.788
Don't you start in. too.

24
00:01:11.989 --> 00:01:13.832
They put me in charge
of a bunch of Johnny Newcomes

25
00:01:14.032 --> 00:01:15.830
barely old enough to shave.

26
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:18.537
There's nothing down
in that mine for 'em to hear.

27
00:01:24.042 --> 00:01:25.419
Why don't you go on
and get yourself cleaned up.

28
00:01:25.627 --> 00:01:28.130
I'll have your dinner ready
when you get out.

29
00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:33.518
I'm hungry now.

30
00:01:33.719 --> 00:01:35.471
It's not ready.

31
00:02:26.438 --> 00:02:28.065
What the hell?

32
00:03:04.601 --> 00:03:08.151
- 'Uh. working on your skills?
- Just one. Patience.

33
00:03:10.107 --> 00:03:11.404
Where the bloody hell
have you been?

34
00:03:11.608 --> 00:03:13.155
I had to wait
till the daily double.

35
00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:15.078
It was your only pick
that paid off.

36
00:03:19.574 --> 00:03:22.578
Capnomancy isn't an exact magic.

37
00:03:22.786 --> 00:03:26.256
Divining the future through
the movements of rising smoke

38
00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:28.254
it's a tricky business.

39
00:03:28.458 --> 00:03:31.211
I would think
you'd be an expert.

40
00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:32.888
Saddle up.

41
00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:34.761
We're heading to Pennsylvania.

42
00:03:34.965 --> 00:03:36.057
Now. look at the map.

43
00:03:36.258 --> 00:03:37.851
One of the drops is wet. Mmm.

44
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:41.681
Our destination
is the tiny town of Heddwich.

45
00:03:41.888 --> 00:03:44.892
According to local papers.
a mining boss

46
00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:46.602
was just flash-fried
in his shower.

47
00:03:46.810 --> 00:03:48.278
Well. you're on your own.

48
00:03:48.478 --> 00:03:49.400
Pennsylvania?

49
00:03:49.604 --> 00:03:51.948
The succubus on a freight train?

50
00:03:52.149 --> 00:03:53.822
That warrant still stands?

51
00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:55.197
Funny what a long memory
the law has

52
00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:56.745
when it comes to train
derailments.

53
00:04:27.809 --> 00:04:30.153
Who are you?

54
00:04:31.688 --> 00:04:35.158
You're really starting
to piss me off.

55
00:04:52.083 --> 00:04:54.506
Oh. I'm so sorry.

56
00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:58.382
Oh. Well. the apologies
are all mine. luv.

57
00:04:58.590 --> 00:05:00.638
Let's. uh. get you sorted. yeah?

58
00:05:00.842 --> 00:05:02.515
If there's one thing
I know my way around

59
00:05:02.719 --> 00:05:05.347
it's rubbish.

60
00:05:05.555 --> 00:05:08.058
It's... you. You're you.

61
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.940
That observation always ends

62
00:05:11.144 --> 00:05:14.318
in the same way.
and it's never in my favor.

63
00:05:14.523 --> 00:05:16.651
I dream about you.

64
00:05:16.858 --> 00:05:21.113
I... was starting to believe
you weren't real.

65
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:24.291
Who are you?

66
00:05:27.202 --> 00:05:30.126
Some kind of carnival
quick-draw artist. are we?

67
00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:32.298
Perched and peeking in a window.

68
00:05:32.499 --> 00:05:34.297
Scratch out the visage
of some poor lonely sod

69
00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:37.926
and then bump into him as if
you're his long-lost lover.

70
00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:41.178
Tongue in his ear.
hand in his pocket. I bet.

71
00:05:41.383 --> 00:05:43.056
It's a nice play. luv. but
I think I'll sit this one out.

72
00:05:43.260 --> 00:05:46.981
No. It's the dirty blond hair.
The curled lip.

73
00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:48.807
- The bad posture.
- I have excellent posture.

74
00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:52.019
- I've seen it all.
- Well. not well. apparently.

75
00:05:56.565 --> 00:05:59.535
There.

76
00:05:59.734 --> 00:06:01.361
Eyes are much darker
than this one.

77
00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:05.120
No. I don't know who you are.

78
00:06:05.323 --> 00:06:06.996
Please.

79
00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:08.918
(0K3)!-

80
00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:12.043
You want answers.

81
00:06:12.247 --> 00:06:14.796
One artist to another.

82
00:06:16.459 --> 00:06:18.257
In light..

83
00:06:18.461 --> 00:06:20.088
...l always find mine.

84
00:06:34.436 --> 00:06:36.438
"John Constantine."

85
00:06:45.363 --> 00:06:47.240
Stout.

86
00:06:50.035 --> 00:06:53.505
That kind of irony
is hard to ignore. isn't it?

87
00:06:53.705 --> 00:06:56.003
The town's symbol
being a dragon and..

88
00:06:56.207 --> 00:06:58.926
This sorry soul being
burned alive.

89
00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:02.510
So what's your take
on what happened?

90
00:07:02.714 --> 00:07:04.216
Fire through the pipes?
It's rare.

91
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.767
But it happens in mining towns.

92
00:07:05.967 --> 00:07:07.514
Well. maybe if there's fracking.

93
00:07:07.719 --> 00:07:09.813
But isn't this the land
of hard rock mining?

94
00:07:10.013 --> 00:07:11.230
What do you know about it?

95
00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:13.684
Grew up in Liverpool. mate.

96
00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:16.520
Breathed in more coal dust
than fresh air as a lad.

97
00:07:16.728 --> 00:07:17.570
Lannis!

98
00:07:17.771 --> 00:07:19.523
Hean

99
00:07:19.731 --> 00:07:21.608
Must've been a good bloke.

100
00:07:21.816 --> 00:07:24.160
Lannis was a bastard.

101
00:07:24.361 --> 00:07:26.159
But they closed the mine
for the day.

102
00:07:26.363 --> 00:07:27.785
Fellas around here
don't need an invitation

103
00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:29.161
to get a skinful.

104
00:07:29.366 --> 00:07:31.869
Another pitcher. Charlie.

105
00:07:32.077 --> 00:07:35.627
Have you considered actual
dragons as the guilty party?

106
00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:37.252
There's no natural explanation
of what happened

107
00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:38.709
to poor Lannis. is there?

108
00:07:38.917 --> 00:07:39.759
You got that right.

109
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:40.802
But it weren't no dragon

110
00:07:41.002 --> 00:07:43.130
that took Lannis and the others.

111
00:07:43.338 --> 00:07:44.214
- The others?
- Nine others.

112
00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:46.720
All in the last year.

113
00:07:46.925 --> 00:07:49.474
They died like this bloke?

114
00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:51.396
Mining accidents.

115
00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:53.690
Some of the boys are saying
we dug a little too deep.

116
00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:54.937
We knocked on the door of hell

117
00:07:55.141 --> 00:07:57.143
and now hell is knocking back.

118
00:07:57.352 --> 00:07:59.229
- Someone heard knocking?
- Yeah.

119
00:07:59.437 --> 00:08:01.860
Down in that godforsaken tunnel.

120
00:08:30.093 --> 00:08:31.470
Whoa!

121
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:22.352
Find what you're looking for?

122
00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:25.811
As a matter of fact. no.

123
00:11:26.019 --> 00:11:29.068
My name's John Constantine.
Philly Enquirer.

124
00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:32.071
I didn't notice you out front
with all the others.

125
00:11:33.276 --> 00:11:35.153
I've been hiding back here.

126
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:38.160
My husband's death
hit me very hard.

127
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:41.163
You've got some. uh. coal there.

128
00:11:41.367 --> 00:11:42.960
On your arm.

129
00:11:43.161 --> 00:11:44.333
Oh.

130
00:11:44.537 --> 00:11:46.790
You can't escape it around here.

131
00:11:46.998 --> 00:11:49.717
The soot. The grime.

132
00:11:49.918 --> 00:11:52.888
Seeps into every pore and fiber.

133
00:11:53.087 --> 00:11:55.636
Uh. this doesn't
really make sense. does it?

134
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.184
And if you don't mind
me asking

135
00:11:58.384 --> 00:11:59.727
what do you think happened?

136
00:11:59.928 --> 00:12:03.432
Does it really matter?
Lannis is gone.

137
00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:05.267
Well. if you help me.
I might write a story

138
00:12:05.475 --> 00:12:06.943
that celebrates his life.

139
00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:11.649
Because our life
was just one big celebration.

140
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:14.405
Sorry.

141
00:12:15.401 --> 00:12:18.530
You're sweet.

142
00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:21.582
You know. I've heard rumors
that there's..

143
00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:25.538
Something not natural
down in that mine.

144
00:12:25.745 --> 00:12:27.543
Your husband
ever talk about it?

145
00:12:27.747 --> 00:12:29.215
You want a story?

146
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:30.291
Yeah.

147
00:12:30.500 --> 00:12:34.004
Okay. I have one for you.

148
00:12:34.212 --> 00:12:36.180
It's about a Romani girl.

149
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:41.137
She got letters from a man.
a rich man..

150
00:12:41.344 --> 00:12:44.848
Who wanted to marry her.
Make her his queen.

151
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:49.815
Said he was the captain
of industry.

152
00:12:50.019 --> 00:12:52.693
Failed to mention it was coal.

153
00:12:52.897 --> 00:12:56.117
Now. will that story
sell papers?

154
00:12:56.317 --> 00:12:58.240
We can talk at a later date.
It's fine.

155
00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.993
Why?

156
00:13:01.197 --> 00:13:03.916
I'm free now.

157
00:13:07.912 --> 00:13:09.084
Uh..

158
00:13:11.416 --> 00:13:12.542
Look. you're a lovely bird
and everything...

159
00:13:12.750 --> 00:13:13.967
- Out.
- But I'm not being..

160
00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:15.504
- Out!
- Alright. I'm going.

161
00:13:15.712 --> 00:13:17.180
Alright. I'm leaving.

162
00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:19.303
- Get out.
- I'm going.

163
00:13:19.507 --> 00:13:21.305
- I want you gone.
- Alright. alright. I'm going.

164
00:13:21.509 --> 00:13:22.476
There's no need
to cause a fuss. right?

165
00:13:22.677 --> 00:13:23.849
Someone get him out.
I want him out.

166
00:13:24.053 --> 00:13:26.556
Who is this?

167
00:13:26.764 --> 00:13:28.892
He says he's a reporter.

168
00:13:29.100 --> 00:13:31.148
- Yeah.
- Hey. Hey.

169
00:13:31.352 --> 00:13:34.572
Hey! Nobody messes
with my people.

170
00:13:37.734 --> 00:13:39.736
What is it you want here?

171
00:13:39.944 --> 00:13:43.994
It's as the lady said.
I'm a reporter.

172
00:13:45.158 --> 00:13:46.876
Check him.

173
00:13:57.045 --> 00:13:58.217
Now. I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

174
00:13:58.421 --> 00:14:02.051
- Oh.
- Who the hell are you?

175
00:14:02.258 --> 00:14:03.726
I take it you're the boss
of the mine.

176
00:14:03.926 --> 00:14:07.271
Yes. I'm the president
of the NorPenn Mining Company.

177
00:14:07.472 --> 00:14:10.521
You're upsetting the widow
of one of my respected men.

178
00:14:10.725 --> 00:14:12.318
We both know that's not true.

179
00:14:12.518 --> 00:14:13.861
Take it easy. Thad.

180
00:14:14.062 --> 00:14:17.157
He might be with Environmental
Protection.

181
00:14:17.357 --> 00:14:18.859
This one? No chance.

182
00:14:19.067 --> 00:14:22.571
Oh. in a way. your associate
there is not wrong.

183
00:14:22.779 --> 00:14:26.249
You've got a not-so-natural
disaster down in that mine.

184
00:14:26.449 --> 00:14:29.123
You know it and I know it.

185
00:14:29.327 --> 00:14:31.705
What I can't figure out
is why it's come above ground

186
00:14:31.913 --> 00:14:35.008
to kill one of your men.

187
00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:37.051
You listen to me.

188
00:14:37.251 --> 00:14:38.503
I don't know what sleazy tabloid

189
00:14:38.711 --> 00:14:40.554
you write for. but I got
my hands filled here

190
00:14:40.755 --> 00:14:42.382
with scared miners.

191
00:14:42.548 --> 00:14:45.017
The biggest threat to them
are parasites like you spreading

192
00:14:45.218 --> 00:14:47.186
panic and fear.

193
00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:52.025
You heard it as well.
didn't you?

194
00:14:54.060 --> 00:14:55.812
The knocking.

195
00:14:57.897 --> 00:14:59.774
Go home.

196
00:15:27.218 --> 00:15:28.845
Well. I'll give you this..

197
00:15:29.053 --> 00:15:31.727
You are persistent.

198
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:33.274
The honeymoon suite?

199
00:15:33.474 --> 00:15:35.602
I always get
the honeymoon suite.

200
00:15:35.810 --> 00:15:37.528
Lots of extra space.

201
00:15:37.728 --> 00:15:40.072
There's a good energy to it.

202
00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:41.741
You dropped this.

203
00:15:46.904 --> 00:15:48.451
There was 90 quid in there.

204
00:15:48.656 --> 00:15:51.660
You must have dropped that. too.

205
00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:53.415
You know. I described you
to the very nice young man

206
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:55.667
at the front desk. and he said

207
00:15:55.872 --> 00:15:59.217
you're registered
under the name of. um. Caligari.

208
00:15:59.417 --> 00:16:01.511
Bud Caligari.

209
00:16:01.711 --> 00:16:04.555
But your ID
and the boarding pass

210
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:05.927
I found in the trash can

211
00:16:06.132 --> 00:16:07.759
says your name
is John Constantine.

212
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:09.435
The rubbish again?

213
00:16:09.635 --> 00:16:12.479
You're a girl
after my own heart... Zed.

214
00:16:12.638 --> 00:16:13.639
How do you know my name?

215
00:16:13.848 --> 00:16:15.270
Credit card receipt
from your trash.

216
00:16:15.475 --> 00:16:16.727
So I did make an impression.

217
00:16:16.934 --> 00:16:18.527
Well. call me balmy.
but I like to know

218
00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:19.570
who's stalking me.

219
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:21.147
I'm not stalking you.

220
00:16:21.355 --> 00:16:23.449
You know. you've just been
in my head for months.

221
00:16:23.649 --> 00:16:25.276
And then. you know.
all of a sudden. you're here?

222
00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:26.452
Don't you want to know why?

223
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:27.494
I don't seek answers
to questions

224
00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:28.529
that needn't be asked.

225
00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:29.785
Well. I do.

226
00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:30.831
I don't know anything about you

227
00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:31.957
but I feel like I should.

228
00:16:32.158 --> 00:16:33.375
Running into each other today

229
00:16:33.576 --> 00:16:34.623
that's destiny.

230
00:16:34.827 --> 00:16:36.079
Well. if it's destiny that
you're after

231
00:16:36.287 --> 00:16:37.664
then maybe you should take
that 90 quid

232
00:16:37.872 --> 00:16:39.044
and put it on the lottery.

233
00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:40.465
You mean something to me.

234
00:16:40.666 --> 00:16:41.667
You know. and maybe

235
00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:43.093
I mean something to you. too.

236
00:16:43.294 --> 00:16:45.763
A reason to elevate my personal
security.

237
00:16:45.963 --> 00:16:48.637
I have visions I can't control.

238
00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:51.515
And sometimes. feelings.

239
00:16:51.719 --> 00:16:54.598
Listen. Zed..

240
00:16:54.805 --> 00:16:56.648
I'm starting to like you.
A little bit.

241
00:16:56.849 --> 00:16:57.975
But not enough to let you stay

242
00:16:58.184 --> 00:16:59.811
so if you don't mind.
would you..

243
00:17:01.229 --> 00:17:03.732
What is that?

244
00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:06.193
Loneliness.

245
00:17:06.400 --> 00:17:07.822
Pain.

246
00:17:08.027 --> 00:17:09.700
Desperation.

247
00:17:11.531 --> 00:17:13.875
These things motivate you.

248
00:17:16.494 --> 00:17:19.794
What kind of person
is motivated by these things?

249
00:17:23.334 --> 00:17:26.929
So much guilt. John Constantine.

250
00:17:32.009 --> 00:17:36.059
Clairsentient.

251
00:17:36.264 --> 00:17:39.063
Or maybe just a good guesser.

252
00:17:39.267 --> 00:17:41.110
(0K3)!-

253
00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:43.529
You want answers?

254
00:17:43.729 --> 00:17:45.106
Let's see what you got.

255
00:17:45.314 --> 00:17:47.658
Park it.

256
00:17:47.858 --> 00:17:50.031
You'll do everything I say.
you understand?

257
00:17:50.236 --> 00:17:52.238
- Yes.
- Close your eyes.

258
00:17:53.781 --> 00:17:56.125
I want you to see an image
in your mind.

259
00:17:56.325 --> 00:17:58.168
It's a total whiteout.

260
00:17:58.369 --> 00:18:00.167
Absorbing all sound

261
00:18:00.371 --> 00:18:05.468
except for the sound
of my voice.

262
00:18:06.669 --> 00:18:09.297
Are you with me?

263
00:18:09.505 --> 00:18:12.475
Good.

264
00:18:12.675 --> 00:18:15.269
There's a white dove
lost in the snowstorm.

265
00:18:15.469 --> 00:18:17.437
You need to save it.

266
00:18:18.889 --> 00:18:21.608
Hold out your hand.
Open your senses.

267
00:18:21.809 --> 00:18:25.439
And let the dove come to you..

268
00:18:25.646 --> 00:18:27.068
Now.

269
00:18:33.487 --> 00:18:35.581
Zed.

270
00:18:35.781 --> 00:18:36.748
Zed!

271
00:18:39.869 --> 00:18:41.917
Zed. Zed.

272
00:18:49.086 --> 00:18:51.259
You saw the fire.

273
00:18:53.090 --> 00:18:57.095
Was that the man
in town who was burning?

274
00:18:57.303 --> 00:19:00.102
What else did you see?

275
00:19:00.306 --> 00:19:02.775
A tall cross.

276
00:19:04.769 --> 00:19:06.567
Alright.

277
00:19:06.771 --> 00:19:08.614
You did a cracking job.

278
00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:10.691
Well. we're on to something.
you and me.

279
00:19:13.319 --> 00:19:15.993
I'm just gonna take
a quick change

280
00:19:16.155 --> 00:19:18.908
then we're gonna get to the
bottom of this. alright?

281
00:19:19.116 --> 00:19:20.868
Good.

282
00:19:29.835 --> 00:19:31.337
John?

283
00:19:38.886 --> 00:19:41.856
John?

284
00:19:42.056 --> 00:19:43.774
Constantine!

285
00:20:10.626 --> 00:20:13.755
You'll make yourself known
if you know what's good for you.

286
00:20:23.639 --> 00:20:25.516
Really?

287
00:20:25.725 --> 00:20:28.695
- In a church?
- 'Sorry.

288
00:20:28.894 --> 00:20:30.896
Don't apologize to me. mate.

289
00:20:33.023 --> 00:20:35.025
Put your clothes on. will you?

290
00:20:38.446 --> 00:20:40.790
- What's this business?
- Just a story.

291
00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:43.459
You know. meant to be scary.

292
00:20:43.659 --> 00:20:45.661
Tall man. no face.

293
00:20:45.870 --> 00:20:47.213
Follows you home.
peeps in your window.

294
00:20:47.413 --> 00:20:50.542
It's. it's not very original.

295
00:20:51.834 --> 00:20:53.427
Alright. go on. Run home.

296
00:20:53.627 --> 00:20:55.095
Alright.

297
00:22:11.956 --> 00:22:14.926
Have you seen an English man?
Who wears a trench coat?

298
00:22:15.125 --> 00:22:16.297
Stick you with a bar tab. too?

299
00:22:17.837 --> 00:22:19.805
My advice. don't waste
yourself on that one.

300
00:22:20.005 --> 00:22:21.348
I don't have a choice.

301
00:22:21.549 --> 00:22:23.972
My son had that effect..

302
00:22:24.176 --> 00:22:26.429
When he was alive.

303
00:22:26.637 --> 00:22:29.015
Left behind clutches
of weepy girls

304
00:22:29.223 --> 00:22:32.477
who swore he was the only one
to give their life meaning.

305
00:22:33.602 --> 00:22:36.230
It's not like that.

306
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:39.942
It's like that.
but not the way you think.

307
00:22:40.150 --> 00:22:44.030
I mean. it's just that...
he means something to me.

308
00:22:44.238 --> 00:22:45.080
I don't know what.

309
00:22:45.281 --> 00:22:46.123
Well. there was a time when

310
00:22:46.323 --> 00:22:47.825
people came to me for answers.

311
00:22:49.285 --> 00:22:51.413
But now our barkeep
hears more confessions

312
00:22:51.620 --> 00:22:53.748
in one day than I used to hear
in a month of Sundays.

313
00:22:53.956 --> 00:22:57.130
- 'Here you go.
- Thank you.

314
00:23:00.004 --> 00:23:03.099
So. your son's the reason
you left your faith?

315
00:23:03.299 --> 00:23:06.052
I left the church
when the mine swallowed him.

316
00:23:08.846 --> 00:23:11.941
But I didn't leave my faith.

317
00:23:12.141 --> 00:23:14.769
Can't say I had much
to begin with.

318
00:23:14.977 --> 00:23:17.696
Faith is an unshakable
acceptance

319
00:23:17.897 --> 00:23:19.319
with no room for doubt.

320
00:23:21.233 --> 00:23:24.282
I'll never have that now.

321
00:23:24.486 --> 00:23:26.409
Cursed mine has seen to that.

322
00:23:45.424 --> 00:23:47.347
Hello. luv.
Is it mornin' already?

323
00:23:47.551 --> 00:23:49.645
You leave when I want you

324
00:23:49.845 --> 00:23:52.689
and you're here when I don't.

325
00:23:52.890 --> 00:23:55.894
I'll make it easy for you.

326
00:23:56.101 --> 00:23:57.523
Get out! Get up!

327
00:23:57.728 --> 00:24:00.277
- Oh. don't be that way. luv.
- I don't want you!

328
00:24:00.481 --> 00:24:03.109
I had to verify that
which you provided.

329
00:24:03.317 --> 00:24:05.285
A strict security protocol
is. in fact

330
00:24:05.486 --> 00:24:06.908
required in my business.

331
00:24:07.112 --> 00:24:09.865
I still don't know what you do.

332
00:24:11.367 --> 00:24:13.870
What I am. as you have so..

333
00:24:14.078 --> 00:24:16.251
Mconventionally portrayed

334
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.128
an exorcist. demonologist

335
00:24:18.332 --> 00:24:22.587
and occasional dabbler
in the dark arts.

336
00:24:22.795 --> 00:24:25.890
Now. the question is..

337
00:24:26.090 --> 00:24:27.012
Who are you?

338
00:24:27.216 --> 00:24:28.468
- I'm Zed.
- Right.

339
00:24:28.676 --> 00:24:30.553
Zed Martin.

340
00:24:30.761 --> 00:24:32.559
I found your three-month lease.

341
00:24:32.763 --> 00:24:36.233
So. what's a chica bonita
in her mid-20s

342
00:24:36.433 --> 00:24:39.562
doing slumming it in a one-horse
Welsh mining town

343
00:24:39.770 --> 00:24:41.693
in the middle of Pennsylvania?

344
00:24:41.897 --> 00:24:42.864
I travel a lot.

345
00:24:43.065 --> 00:24:45.443
Right.

346
00:24:45.651 --> 00:24:49.781
Well. there's only two types
of people who travel a lot.

347
00:24:49.989 --> 00:24:52.538
Those in the circus and..

348
00:24:52.741 --> 00:24:55.745
Those on the run. and curiously

349
00:24:55.953 --> 00:25:00.459
I'm not seeing any funny wigs
or face paint.

350
00:25:00.666 --> 00:25:03.419
I know what I'm running from.
Do you?

351
00:25:03.627 --> 00:25:06.676
You came to me. not the other
way around.

352
00:25:06.880 --> 00:25:09.053
You step into my world

353
00:25:09.258 --> 00:25:12.011
you'll be staring down demons.
devils and the like.

354
00:25:12.219 --> 00:25:15.314
Those things in your paintings
they're real.

355
00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:18.267
Yeah.

356
00:25:18.475 --> 00:25:21.228
It won't be bad memories

357
00:25:21.437 --> 00:25:23.940
nipping at your heels

358
00:25:24.148 --> 00:25:26.651
but the scourge of hell
gunning for your soul.

359
00:25:26.859 --> 00:25:29.829
And when the bell rings

360
00:25:30.029 --> 00:25:31.656
then you'd best be ready.
willing and able

361
00:25:31.864 --> 00:25:34.367
to answer with something
far more deadly

362
00:25:34.575 --> 00:25:37.328
than a charcoal pencil.

363
00:25:37.536 --> 00:25:39.880
Now. if you can handle that.
then we can talk business.

364
00:25:40.080 --> 00:25:42.833
If not. then we go
our separate ways

365
00:25:43.042 --> 00:25:46.546
and I never see your
pretty little face again.

366
00:25:49.423 --> 00:25:51.016
I ain't going nowhere.

367
00:25:56.263 --> 00:25:57.765
Is that what I think it is?

368
00:25:57.973 --> 00:25:59.395
A mine collapse.

369
00:26:08.609 --> 00:26:11.203
Hey. Hey. what happened here?

370
00:26:13.238 --> 00:26:16.287
It all came down
right on top of us.

371
00:26:16.492 --> 00:26:18.915
Before it happened. knocking.

372
00:26:19.119 --> 00:26:20.041
Did you hear knocking?

373
00:26:20.245 --> 00:26:22.589
Yeah. It's in there.

374
00:26:28.921 --> 00:26:31.470
Alright. Thanks. mate.

375
00:26:38.847 --> 00:26:40.474
John!

376
00:26:46.563 --> 00:26:48.110
If Thad catches you here.
he's gonna make good...

377
00:26:48.273 --> 00:26:50.901
Men are dying in your mine.

378
00:26:55.864 --> 00:26:58.117
Five years ago.
Heddwich was dead.

379
00:26:58.283 --> 00:26:59.409
NorPenn saved this town.

380
00:26:59.618 --> 00:27:00.961
They-they. they said the mine

381
00:27:01.161 --> 00:27:02.879
was tapped out.
but we gave it new life.

382
00:27:03.080 --> 00:27:06.050
Because you're a rogue
operation. digging unauthorized

383
00:27:06.250 --> 00:27:07.422
tunnels into regions
of the earth

384
00:27:07.626 --> 00:27:10.721
where mortal man
has no rightful place.

385
00:27:10.921 --> 00:27:12.719
It's true. isn't it?

386
00:27:12.923 --> 00:27:14.550
What the miners are saying?

387
00:27:16.760 --> 00:27:17.886
They hear sounds?

388
00:27:18.095 --> 00:27:20.518
And they'll keep on hearing them

389
00:27:20.722 --> 00:27:23.771
and people will keep dying

390
00:27:23.976 --> 00:27:26.729
until you shut down that mine.

391
00:27:30.065 --> 00:27:31.362
What is that? What the hell?

392
00:27:37.531 --> 00:27:38.908
We need something to break
the windows now.

393
00:27:39.116 --> 00:27:40.834
Check under the seat.
What the hell?

394
00:27:41.034 --> 00:27:41.876
Damn it!

395
00:28:12.983 --> 00:28:13.950
Are you okay?

396
00:28:14.151 --> 00:28:15.778
Oh. yeah.
I had it under control.

397
00:28:15.986 --> 00:28:16.828
You almost drowned in mud.

398
00:28:17.029 --> 00:28:18.622
No. I was. uh..

399
00:28:18.822 --> 00:28:20.039
Thinking up a spell in my head.

400
00:28:20.240 --> 00:28:22.163
Go check on the driver.

401
00:28:22.367 --> 00:28:24.290
[coughifl9l

402
00:28:38.050 --> 00:28:39.427
Don't torture yourself
over it. luv.

403
00:28:39.635 --> 00:28:41.012
There was nothing we could
do for the blighter

404
00:28:41.220 --> 00:28:42.472
and the last thing we want
to do is stick around

405
00:28:42.679 --> 00:28:43.976
and get drawn into a police
investigation.

406
00:28:44.181 --> 00:28:46.354
I don't understand.
What was in the car?

407
00:28:46.558 --> 00:28:49.061
That's the price of doing
business with yours truly.

408
00:28:49.269 --> 00:28:50.191
I tried to warn you.

409
00:28:50.395 --> 00:28:52.818
I know. I'm still here.

410
00:28:53.023 --> 00:28:55.572
Piss off.
There's nothing to look at.

411
00:28:55.776 --> 00:28:56.868
What's going on?

412
00:28:57.069 --> 00:28:58.867
Back home. our miners

413
00:28:59.071 --> 00:29:00.698
called 'em "Coblynau"

414
00:29:00.906 --> 00:29:02.533
but you see 'em
in every culture.

415
00:29:02.741 --> 00:29:04.368
They're the spirits
of dead miners.

416
00:29:04.576 --> 00:29:07.955
They knock on walls
to warn of danger.

417
00:29:08.163 --> 00:29:11.667
So. these Coblynau..
They're protecting the miners?

418
00:29:11.875 --> 00:29:13.092
They warn them of danger
instead of causing it?

419
00:29:13.293 --> 00:29:15.421
That's right.

420
00:29:15.629 --> 00:29:18.348
Traditional Coblynau.
they never rise to the surface

421
00:29:18.548 --> 00:29:20.642
and they certainly don't murder.

422
00:29:20.842 --> 00:29:22.560
So. what's the explanation?

423
00:29:22.761 --> 00:29:24.513
Could be the Rising Darkness.

424
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:28.066
Something's forcing evil
to the surface in waves.

425
00:29:28.267 --> 00:29:30.110
It's changing the rules.

426
00:29:30.310 --> 00:29:33.359
I'm sensing a little
of the human touch.

427
00:29:33.563 --> 00:29:37.158
Like someone's... calling
these spirits on purpose.

428
00:29:37.359 --> 00:29:40.954
Nothing says payback better
than death by demon.

429
00:29:41.154 --> 00:29:43.156
If I'm right

430
00:29:43.365 --> 00:29:46.164
then someone's conjuring
these bad boys from close by.

431
00:29:46.368 --> 00:29:48.245
Like a miner.

432
00:29:48.453 --> 00:29:49.921
I heard that they're all
gathering at the pub

433
00:29:50.122 --> 00:29:51.795
for an emergency meeting.

434
00:29:51.999 --> 00:29:54.878
Think we need to change. luv.
I'll meet you there.

435
00:29:57.796 --> 00:29:59.969
Alright. look. if you're
just gonna fly off the handle

436
00:30:00.132 --> 00:30:02.351
and turn this into
some kind of a spook show

437
00:30:02.551 --> 00:30:04.679
then I have nothing to say
to you right now.

438
00:30:04.886 --> 00:30:05.728
Crazy rumors
aren't gonna help anyone..

439
00:30:05.929 --> 00:30:07.055
Curious.

440
00:30:07.264 --> 00:30:09.608
Skeptical drunks
nowhere to be seen.

441
00:30:09.808 --> 00:30:11.401
You mean the ex-priest?

442
00:30:11.601 --> 00:30:12.773
- Come again?
- Ellis.

443
00:30:12.978 --> 00:30:14.696
He used to be a priest

444
00:30:14.896 --> 00:30:17.945
before his. uh.
son died in the mines.

445
00:30:18.150 --> 00:30:21.825
Which could be a good cause
for payback.

446
00:30:22.029 --> 00:30:23.827
When I gave you the slip
yesterday

447
00:30:24.031 --> 00:30:26.250
I found evidence of one of those
slurry things being raised

448
00:30:26.450 --> 00:30:28.373
in an abandoned church
outside of town.

449
00:30:28.577 --> 00:30:31.205
The church that Ellis turned
his back on.

450
00:30:31.413 --> 00:30:35.714
So. he could be the one that's
conjuring the evil for revenge?

451
00:30:35.917 --> 00:30:39.296
Come with me.
I'm taking you for a spin.

452
00:30:39.504 --> 00:30:41.177
Excuse me. mate. um.
but. look. my lady

453
00:30:41.381 --> 00:30:42.633
she's having
a bit of a turn. you know?

454
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:44.218
Do you mind if we commandeer
your seat right here?

455
00:30:44.426 --> 00:30:48.772
Is that alright?
Oh. thanks a lot. mate. Thanks.

456
00:30:48.972 --> 00:30:52.897
- Take a seat.
- I get it. okay?

457
00:30:53.101 --> 00:30:54.728
This is his stool.
his spot. where he drinks

458
00:30:54.936 --> 00:30:55.903
but I can't control my visions.

459
00:30:56.104 --> 00:30:57.697
Well. you did yesterday.

460
00:30:57.898 --> 00:31:01.619
Just remember what I told you.
Now close your eyes.

461
00:31:05.030 --> 00:31:06.998
Lock out the world.

462
00:31:10.619 --> 00:31:11.666
It's cold.

463
00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:14.498
- What's that. luv?
- My feet.

464
00:31:14.706 --> 00:31:19.132
Slowly. without losing
the vision. open your eyes.

465
00:31:24.383 --> 00:31:25.680
Look at your feet.

466
00:31:30.180 --> 00:31:32.274
There's a river.

467
00:31:32.474 --> 00:31:34.351
There's a waterfall.

468
00:31:34.559 --> 00:31:36.277
Stay in the vision.

469
00:31:36.478 --> 00:31:37.604
Look for clues.

470
00:31:37.813 --> 00:31:39.861
There's a... tent

471
00:31:40.065 --> 00:31:41.362
and an old chair in front of it.

472
00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:43.284
Like a sofa chair.

473
00:31:43.485 --> 00:31:45.533
Looks like a campground.

474
00:31:45.737 --> 00:31:47.284
You two decide yet?

475
00:31:47.489 --> 00:31:49.412
Charlie. is there a..

476
00:31:49.616 --> 00:31:52.711
A campground on a river
hereabouts?

477
00:31:52.911 --> 00:31:54.413
Rooster Creek's the closest.

478
00:31:54.621 --> 00:31:56.589
Rooster Creek.

479
00:31:56.790 --> 00:31:58.087
How can such a weak man
be capable

480
00:31:58.291 --> 00:31:59.292
of so much destruction?

481
00:31:59.501 --> 00:32:00.343
Well. people aren't all good

482
00:32:00.544 --> 00:32:02.171
and they aren't all wicked.

483
00:32:02.379 --> 00:32:04.802
Here. bristles up
to ward off evil.

484
00:32:05.006 --> 00:32:07.134
- What are you gonna use?
- My wits.

485
00:32:11.805 --> 00:32:14.183
Are you the Pastor Ellis McGee
of the Good Shepherd Church

486
00:32:14.391 --> 00:32:15.734
of St. Asaph?

487
00:32:15.934 --> 00:32:18.403
Not anymore.

488
00:32:34.995 --> 00:32:37.043
- You know it.
- Of course I know it.

489
00:32:37.247 --> 00:32:39.591
The Breastplate of St. Patrick.

490
00:32:39.791 --> 00:32:41.259
What the hell's going on here?

491
00:32:41.460 --> 00:32:43.804
I'm here to end
your spiritual warfare.

492
00:32:44.004 --> 00:32:45.597
Your skills
to channel the divine

493
00:32:45.797 --> 00:32:47.674
can also be used
to unleash evil.

494
00:32:47.883 --> 00:32:49.430
You think I'm behind
the killings in this town?

495
00:32:49.634 --> 00:32:52.513
Your desecrated church
has all the power of evil

496
00:32:52.721 --> 00:32:53.847
you need. mate.

497
00:32:54.055 --> 00:32:55.853
You need faith to raise evil.

498
00:32:56.057 --> 00:32:56.899
In case you haven't noticed here

499
00:32:57.100 --> 00:33:00.229
I'm all tapped out.

500
00:33:00.437 --> 00:33:02.439
You know. John.
maybe we should listen to him.

501
00:33:02.647 --> 00:33:04.365
Fools. You got to get your
head out of the hogwash.

502
00:33:04.566 --> 00:33:06.193
You can't even see the facts
right in front of you.

503
00:33:06.401 --> 00:33:07.698
Like what?

504
00:33:07.903 --> 00:33:09.450
The men killed aboveground

505
00:33:09.654 --> 00:33:12.077
they're not miners...
they're the bosses in charge.

506
00:33:12.282 --> 00:33:14.250
Somebody's
finally making them pay.

507
00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:21.837
You might be right.

508
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.502
How many of the bosses are left?

509
00:33:23.668 --> 00:33:27.047
Just one. Owner
of the company. Thad Bowman.

510
00:33:27.255 --> 00:33:28.677
You have art supplies
in your car. right?

511
00:33:28.882 --> 00:33:30.759
Yeah.

512
00:33:30.967 --> 00:33:33.265
Spray paint's what we need.

513
00:33:33.470 --> 00:33:35.188
Come on.

514
00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:42.354
Coming. WW?

515
00:33:42.562 --> 00:33:45.566
Yeah. I'm right here. Dad.

516
00:33:45.774 --> 00:33:47.242
Peterson said
he cleared the east shaft

517
00:33:47.442 --> 00:33:48.989
but I also know that
little yellow-belly

518
00:33:49.194 --> 00:33:51.117
was scared to go down there.

519
00:33:51.321 --> 00:33:52.664
I want to see it for myself
before the men

520
00:33:52.864 --> 00:33:54.241
start showing up again
at first light.

521
00:33:54.449 --> 00:33:56.326
Listen. you really think
that this is a good idea

522
00:33:56.535 --> 00:33:58.287
opening the mine after
what happened yesterday?

523
00:33:58.495 --> 00:34:00.168
Men want to work. boy.

524
00:34:00.372 --> 00:34:01.874
You got to respect that.

525
00:34:16.388 --> 00:34:18.311
It looks clear to me.

526
00:34:18.515 --> 00:34:20.438
Let's check the down shaft.

527
00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:30.573
You really think
we should be doing this?

528
00:34:30.777 --> 00:34:33.701
Don't you start. boy.

529
00:34:37.993 --> 00:34:39.711
Nathan!

530
00:34:49.087 --> 00:34:51.055
It is real.

531
00:34:51.256 --> 00:34:53.179
Paint.

532
00:35:01.433 --> 00:35:03.731
Protector of Earth.

533
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:07.815
Guardian of the Soils
of Foundation

534
00:35:08.023 --> 00:35:11.368
be welcome in this sacred space.

535
00:35:11.568 --> 00:35:13.912
By the Earth that is your body

536
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:18.037
and the wisdom of the ancients.

537
00:35:18.241 --> 00:35:21.040
Hail and farewell.

538
00:35:31.588 --> 00:35:32.555
What did we do?

539
00:35:32.756 --> 00:35:35.384
I reminded it of what it is.

540
00:35:35.592 --> 00:35:37.640
A protective spirit.

541
00:35:37.844 --> 00:35:41.815
As I said. Coblynau
are peaceful buggers at heart.

542
00:35:45.185 --> 00:35:48.155
He's still breathing. He's okay.

543
00:35:48.355 --> 00:35:49.948
This one's not so lucky.

544
00:35:54.986 --> 00:35:56.954
So we're back
where we started from.

545
00:35:58.823 --> 00:36:01.201
These handprints..

546
00:36:01.409 --> 00:36:02.706
I've seen this before.

547
00:36:02.911 --> 00:36:05.664
Where?

548
00:36:05.872 --> 00:36:09.001
We need to make sure that
no one comes down here again.

549
00:36:09.209 --> 00:36:10.586
Even Take him home.

550
00:36:10.794 --> 00:36:11.966
What are you gonna do?

551
00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:14.548
There's only one thing
I can think of.

552
00:36:25.809 --> 00:36:27.106
What's the priest doing here?

553
00:36:27.310 --> 00:36:29.563
He needs to be here to see this.

554
00:36:31.606 --> 00:36:32.573
You did good earlier.

555
00:36:32.774 --> 00:36:34.026
If I failed to mention it.

556
00:36:34.234 --> 00:36:35.736
Well. now I know
what line of work you do.

557
00:36:35.944 --> 00:36:37.787
It's not for everyone. luv.

558
00:36:39.322 --> 00:36:43.202
So. after this. you find
a nice. quiet new town?

559
00:36:44.744 --> 00:36:46.246
Yeah.

560
00:36:46.454 --> 00:36:48.877
Because I'm that kind of. uh..

561
00:36:49.082 --> 00:36:51.631
Chica Bonita.

562
00:36:51.835 --> 00:36:55.885
We really don't want
to be standing here.

563
00:36:56.089 --> 00:36:57.636
Sometimes appeals of faith
just need

564
00:36:57.841 --> 00:37:00.685
a little time to be answered.

565
00:37:00.885 --> 00:37:02.478
Care to do the honors?

566
00:37:10.603 --> 00:37:11.980
For my son.

567
00:37:21.948 --> 00:37:24.201
I need your car keys.

568
00:37:24.409 --> 00:37:26.161
They're in the truck.
Where are you going?

569
00:37:26.369 --> 00:37:27.712
To do the hard part. of course.

570
00:37:27.912 --> 00:37:29.585
- We just blew up the mine.
- Oh. that we did.

571
00:37:29.789 --> 00:37:32.133
And the Coblynau will stay
at rest if they're left alone.

572
00:37:32.333 --> 00:37:33.926
But someone
with a very powerful magic

573
00:37:34.127 --> 00:37:36.596
summoned them to the surface
in the first place.

574
00:37:37.756 --> 00:37:38.973
This isn't over.

575
00:37:44.345 --> 00:37:46.222
The reporter. right?

576
00:37:46.431 --> 00:37:47.648
Philly Enquirer?

577
00:37:49.392 --> 00:37:50.689
Can I come in?

578
00:37:50.894 --> 00:37:53.647
I'm afraid I have guests.

579
00:37:53.855 --> 00:37:56.404
I know who killed your husband.

580
00:37:56.608 --> 00:37:58.781
In that case..

581
00:37:58.943 --> 00:38:01.366
L think you should meet
my guests.

582
00:38:01.571 --> 00:38:04.745
Well. aren't you going to
invite me in. then?

583
00:38:04.949 --> 00:38:05.791
No need.

584
00:38:10.163 --> 00:38:12.712
Now... you had news for me?

585
00:38:14.375 --> 00:38:16.753
I'll give you one chance.

586
00:38:16.961 --> 00:38:19.259
Send your pets away
and I'll spare you.

587
00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:20.932
How did you know?

588
00:38:21.132 --> 00:38:24.511
The coal mark on your arm
when I first met you.

589
00:38:24.719 --> 00:38:26.437
I saw one just like it
on a young lad

590
00:38:26.638 --> 00:38:27.981
the Coblynau
were trying to kill.

591
00:38:28.181 --> 00:38:31.936
And then... l remembered
what you said.

592
00:38:33.436 --> 00:38:35.734
You're Romani.

593
00:38:35.939 --> 00:38:38.408
There's nothing blacker
than gypsy magic.

594
00:38:38.608 --> 00:38:41.202
When I left home.
I promised myself

595
00:38:41.402 --> 00:38:43.404
I'd never use
my family's magic again.

596
00:38:44.739 --> 00:38:46.366
And then
it all came back to me

597
00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:50.329
more powerfully
than ever before.

598
00:38:50.537 --> 00:38:52.084
The only reason
you could do what you did

599
00:38:52.288 --> 00:38:55.337
is because there's
a darkness spreading everywhere

600
00:38:55.542 --> 00:38:58.466
even to lonesome little
backwaters like Heddwich.

601
00:38:58.670 --> 00:39:00.968
It's infecting you.

602
00:39:01.172 --> 00:39:03.300
No. You're wrong.

603
00:39:03.508 --> 00:39:06.853
Send these poor sods back
to where they belong.

604
00:39:11.558 --> 00:39:13.936
Kill him.

605
00:39:17.730 --> 00:39:20.483
You forgot one thing
you stupid bat!

606
00:39:20.692 --> 00:39:22.194
These are the spirits
of dead miners

607
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.829
and your husband.
that you murdered. was a miner!

608
00:39:25.029 --> 00:39:27.452
Oh. restless spirit
of this house

609
00:39:27.657 --> 00:39:30.627
I summon thee
to seek thy revenge!

610
00:39:40.503 --> 00:39:43.473
Lannis? No!

611
00:39:43.673 --> 00:39:45.767
Let go of me! No!

612
00:39:45.967 --> 00:39:47.765
I'm the victim!

613
00:40:13.953 --> 00:40:15.330
Moving in. are we?

614
00:40:15.538 --> 00:40:17.006
You wish.

615
00:40:18.875 --> 00:40:22.505
Well. I'm afraid I'm in no mood
for sparring tonight. darling.

616
00:40:22.712 --> 00:40:24.885
Of course not. You almost died.

617
00:40:29.135 --> 00:40:30.808
I just wanted to make sure
you're okay.

618
00:40:31.012 --> 00:40:33.811
No. you didn't.

619
00:40:34.015 --> 00:40:37.235
You just wanted to make sure
I didn't run out on you again.

620
00:40:37.435 --> 00:40:40.154
- Was that the plan?
- Listen. Zed.

621
00:40:40.355 --> 00:40:42.653
There's no denying
that you provide

622
00:40:42.857 --> 00:40:44.700
moderate value in the field.

623
00:40:44.901 --> 00:40:47.404
- I saved your life.
- Well. that's open to debate.

624
00:40:47.612 --> 00:40:50.161
The truth is. I work best alone.

625
00:40:50.365 --> 00:40:52.208
- Me. too.
- I always put myself first.

626
00:40:52.408 --> 00:40:54.410
That's the only way
I've survived.

627
00:40:54.619 --> 00:40:58.340
Everyone who puts their trust
in me dies.

628
00:41:02.794 --> 00:41:04.842
Okay. you got me.

629
00:41:08.383 --> 00:41:11.557
You see. John..

630
00:41:11.761 --> 00:41:14.310
L've been waiting for you..

631
00:41:14.514 --> 00:41:16.141
And you found me.

632
00:41:16.349 --> 00:41:17.475
I don't know
what I've been waiting for

633
00:41:17.684 --> 00:41:20.654
and you don't know
what you've found.

634
00:41:20.812 --> 00:41:24.157
The question is. are we gonna
help each other out or not?

635
00:41:34.242 --> 00:41:36.665
If you'll excuse me

636
00:41:36.869 --> 00:41:38.917
I'm bloody knackered.

637
00:41:53.011 --> 00:41:55.139
Isuppose it could be liberating

638
00:41:55.346 --> 00:41:57.474
to take a leap of faith

639
00:41:57.682 --> 00:41:59.355
to shrug off the burden of proof

640
00:41:59.559 --> 00:42:01.482
for the promise of hope.

641
00:42:01.686 --> 00:42:04.610
It takes trust
to turn darkness to light.

642
00:42:04.814 --> 00:42:06.282
And those who trust

643
00:42:06.482 --> 00:42:09.486
risk putting their faith
in the wrong hands.

644
00:42:09.694 --> 00:42:12.197
For there are those
who pray for you

645
00:42:12.405 --> 00:42:15.409
and there are those
who prey on you.

646
00:42:17.618 --> 00:42:20.462
And no matter
how careful you are

647
00:42:20.663 --> 00:42:25.294
sometimes you just can't
tell the difference.

648
00:42:25.318 --> 00:42:27.318
http://hiqve.com/
